{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772120993,"nonce":"dGj1iYqSkBfJ1k+SQc2FOvt4rc4=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uMuch","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/284","origin":"github"},"title":"Unify project agent directories under .agents/","message":"## Summary\n\nThe current design has two separate agent directory conventions in project repos:\n\n- `.agents/README.md` (repo root) — agent onboarding guide for the repo\n- `config/agent_context/` (nested in manifest config) — workspace-facing project knowledge, symlinked into the workspace as `.agent/project_knowledge`\n\nFor repos like `unh_marine_autonomy` that serve as both manifest and project, this creates two agent directories with unclear boundaries. The naming and location of `agent_context/` doesn't signal its purpose.\n\n## Proposal\n\nUnify under `.agents/` at the project repo root:\n\n```\n\u003cproject-repo\u003e/\n├── .agents/\n│   ├── README.md               # Agent guide (existing convention)\n│   ├── work-plans/             # Plans for work in this repo\n│   └── workspace-context/      # Manifest role: symlinked into workspace\n│       └── ...\n├── config/                     # Pure manifest config (bootstrap, layers, repos)\n└── \u003cpackages...\u003e\n```\n\n## Changes Required\n\n- Update `setup.sh` symlink target from `config/agent_context/` to `.agents/workspace-context/` (or similar)\n- Update project governance template (#273)\n- Update project agent guide template to reference the new structure\n- Update documentation that references `agent_context/`\n\n## Additional Considerations\n\n### Workspace link in project README\n\nThe template or process that generates `.agents/` for a new project should add a note to the project's README (for humans and agents) that this repo is optionally used with the ROS 2 Agent Workspace, with a link to the workspace repo on GitHub. Projects should be self-explanatory standalone, but discoverable as workspace participants.\n\n### Standalone usage\n\nSome files under `.agents/` are useful even without the workspace — `README.md` and `work-plans/` are repo-local concerns. The `workspace-context/` subdirectory is the only part that assumes workspace integration. The design should make this separation clear so projects that adopt `.agents/` without the workspace aren't confused by workspace-specific structure.\n\n## Related\n\n- #273 — Project governance layout template (should align with this)\n- #274 — Discovery script (needs to know where to look)\n- #275 — gather-project-knowledge skill (reads from symlink target)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}